This setup guide assumes your build environment is setup, and you are running ubuntu

Ubuntu: sudo apt-get install build-essential libtool autoconf automake 

== Install Mongrel2==


	Install ZMQ
		sudo apt-get install uuid-dev
		sudo apt-get install libsqlite3-dev	

		sudo apt-get install uuid-runtime
		wget http://download.zeromq.org/zeromq-2.2.0.tar.gz 
		tar -xzvf zeromq-2.2.0.tar.gz
		cd zeromq-2.2.0/
		./configure
		make 
		sudo make install

	Install Mongrel2
		wget http://mongrel2.org/static/downloads/mongrel2-1.7.5.tar.bz2
		tar -jxvf mongrel2-1.7.5.tar.bz2
		cd mongrel2-1.7.5
		make
		sudo make install


	

Install WSGID
	wget http://wsgid.com/static/downloads/wsgid-0.7.0.tar.bz2
	tar -jzvf wsgid-0.7.0.tar.bz2
	cd wsgid-0.7.0
	sudo python setup.py install

	(this requires python-dev and python-setuptools)

virtualENV
Install DJANGO

Install Postgresql
http://blog.iiilx.com/programming/how-to-install-postgres-on-ubuntu-for-django/


